# **Introduction to the Turing-Roche Strategic Partnership**


Our strategic partnership was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](http://elink.turing.ac._X2NsZGVlPWRtaGxiR3h2YmtCMGRYSnBibWN1WVdNdWRXcyUzZCZyZWNpcGllbnRpZD1jb250YWN0LTQ4ODBhOGMzOTIzY2VjMTE4YzYyMDAyMjQ4NDM0ZmViLTRkM2RiZDlmNjZlZTQ4OTg4YTAwZWRiY2IwZGRlNzNmJmVzaWQ9OTJkNDQwYTgtMGY4OC1lYzExLTkzYjAtMDAyMjQ4NDI0ODkxIn0/kMu-0Xy5RWPNx_SYCXS8UA) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment.

The 'North Star' of our five year partnership is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care.**

We are just at the start of our journey but will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building a strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

You can find more info about our current projects [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

## **Current Opportunities at The Alan Turing Institute and Roche**

![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/group_study_working__0.jpg) 

### **Turing Enrichment Scheme: Applications Open**

**Deadline 23rd February 2022**

Now entering its seventh year, this scheme offer students currently enrolled on a doctoral programme at a UK university the opportunity to enrich their doctoral studies by building connections with the Alan Turing Institute and engaging with its diverse community of researchers. Students can learn new methodologies, build new collaborations and develop research independence. Find out more [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

### **Data Science Education Interest Group: Members Wanted**

A new interest group is being set up at the Turing Institute around Data Science Education. Its aim is to bring together people from a breadth of fields and organisations to identify and address key challenges in research and innovation in data science and AI pedagogy, and its implications for policy. The group will be having a formal launch in the next few months and anyone is welcome to sign up- you can find more info [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

You can also find out more about our other interest groups [here](http://elink.turing.ac._X2NsZGVlPWRtaGxiR3h2YmtCMGRYSnBibWN1WVdNdWRXcyUzZCZyZWNpcGllbnRpZD1jb250YWN0LTQ4ODBhOGMzOTIzY2VjMTE4YzYyMDAyMjQ4NDM0ZmViLTRkM2RiZDlmNjZlZTQ4OTg4YTAwZWRiY2IwZGRlNzNmJmVzaWQ9OTJkNDQwYTgtMGY4OC1lYzExLTkzYjAtMDAyMjQ4NDI0ODkxIn0/awVStIeinNgaWWwatkjrgg)- we're keen to get people from the Roche community and beyond involved in these so do have a browse. If you have any questions you can message the interest group organsier directly. 

### Senior Data Scientist (Real World Data) Job at Roche 

**Deadline 13th February 2022**

A Senior Data Scientist role within the Product Development department where you will develop evidence generation strategies, design and execute studies and develop advanced analytics algorithms and applications using a range of real world data, such as patient registries, electronic medical records, biobanks and clinical trials. Find out more and how to apply [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

## Events

 ![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/ags-0057_800-px-wide.jpg) |


### AI UK

The Turing Institute will be holding its flagship two-day AI conference on 22nd-23rd March 2021, exploring themes around the National AI strategy and topical sessions on trends in data science and AI. You can register for the conference [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

### The Software Sustainability's Collaborations Workshop 

This 4 day series brings together researchers, developers, innovators, managers, publishers, policy makers, leaders and educators to explore best practices and the future of research software. You can register [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

### High Performance Computing (HPC) ReproHack at Warwick

ReproHacks are one-day reproducibility hackathons where particpants attempt to reproduce research from published code and data. This event is the first ReproHack with a HPC format- particpants will attempt to reproduce computationally intensive published research. If you'd like feedback on the reproducibility of your computationally intensive research then please submit your paper (or preprint) for review at the event. You can find out more [here](http://elink.turing.ac.).

### Scientific Lead (Consultant) Diverse Data at Genomics England

Genomics England are recruiting a Scientific Lead for their Diverse Data programme in order to help design and deliver their scientific and research strategy around genetic diversity. The role is on a part time basis (1-4 days a week) for 3- 12 months and is particularly suitable for researchers looking to influence a large government programme. You can find out more and how to apply [here](http://elink.turing.ac.-Z6g).
